# Cursor Cloud specific instructions

## Environment overview

Large monorepo (~80 apps, ~372 packages) using Yarn 4 (Berry), Node.js 22.22.2, Turborepo. Docker required for dev services. Environment fully mirrors `.devcontainer/Dockerfile` and `.devcontainer/lifecycle/` scripts. All 53 env vars are synced from the Ona environment via `ona environment ssh <id> -- env`.

## Ona env var sync

Env vars are pulled from the latest running Ona environment using the Ona CLI (`ona login --token $GITPOD_PAT && ona environment ssh <id> -- env`) and written to `~/.ona_env`. Select the running environment with the newest `metadata.lastStartedAt` value, falling back to `metadata.createdAt`. Both bash and zsh source this file. This includes API keys, npm tokens, Turbo config, Oso config, etc., matching the real dev environment.

## Private npm registries

`NPM_TASKFORCESH_TOKEN`, `NPM_LEVEL_CI_TOKEN`, and `CLOUDSMITH_NPM_TOKEN` are synced from Ona. These are required for `yarn install`.

## Docker dev services

- Set `DOCKER_CPUSET=0-7` (or match `nproc`) - default `0-11` assumes 12+ cores.
- Use `sudo` for `docker compose` commands.
- Raise inotify limits before starting the web stack: `sudo sysctl -w fs.inotify.max_user_watches=2097152 fs.inotify.max_user_instances=4096 fs.inotify.max_queued_events=65536`.
- Configure Docker with a high default `nofile` ulimit (`1048576`) before creating containers. Without this, MongoDB can crash during index builds or snapshot restore with `Too many open files`.
- If Docker is restarted while compose containers exist, stale containerd task state can cause `file exists`; run `docker compose down --remove-orphans`, restart `dockerd`, then start again.
- If MySQL exits with InnoDB `OS error 122` after a daemon restart, remove only the local dev MySQL volume (`docker volume rm obsidian_mysql-data`) and restart the stack.
- MongoDB may crash with "Too many open files" on first startup if Docker `nofile` was not configured - restart after fixing Docker defaults.
- Start infrastructure first, then app services.
- Canonical web startup is `just dev-start-web -d`. This starts Mongo and the full web service group, but it does not restore the staging snapshot; `.devcontainer/util/prepare-dev-services.sh` performs snapshot recovery.
- Full snapshot recovery can be heavy in small Cloud VMs. If it fails late, targeted `mongorestore` for required collections (for example `authusers`, `users`, `domains`, `frameworks`, `frameworksections`) can unblock local login smoke tests.

## System dependencies

- `redis-memory-server` needs `libstdc++` for the linker: `sudo ln -sf /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libstdc++.so.6 /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libstdc++.so`
- Dotfiles gitconfig overrides git credential helper — fix with: `git config credential.helper '!gh auth git-credential'`

## Dotfiles

Cloned from `YanxiChen-gh/Dotfiles` at `~/Dotfiles`. Run `cd ~/Dotfiles && WORK_MACHINE=1 sh install.sh` to set up symlinks, Cursor config, MCP servers, and work tools.
